"<div>\n  <h2>Cheesy Potato Pea Casserole</h2>\n  <h4>Ingredients:</h4>\n  <ul>\n    <li>5 large potatoes, peeled and diced</li>\n    <li>1 cup frozen peas, thawed</li>\n    <li>1 cup shredded cheese</li>\n    <li>1/2 cup crushed crackers</li>\n    <li>1 cup cooked rice</li>\n    <li>1/2 cup milk</li>\n    <li>2 tablespoons butter</li>\n    <li>1/2 teaspoon garlic powder</li>\n    <li>Salt and pepper to taste</li>\n  </ul>\n  <h4>Instructions:</h4>\n  <ol>\n    <li>Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F.</li>\n    <li>In a large pot, boil the diced potatoes until they are fork-tender. Drain and set aside.</li>\n    <li>In a skillet, melt the butter over medium heat. Add the peas and garlic powder. Cook for 3-4 minutes until the peas are tender.</li>\n    <li>Add the cooked rice and stir to combine.</li>\n    <li>In a mixing bowl, combine the cooked potatoes, milk, salt, and pepper. Mash until smooth.</li>\n    <li>In a baking dish, layer half of the mashed potatoes on the bottom.</li>\n    <li>Add the rice and pea mixture on top of the potatoes.</li>\n    <li>Layer the remaining mashed potatoes on top of the rice mixture.</li>\n    <li>Sprinkle the shredded cheese and crushed crackers over the top of the casserole.</li>\n    <li>Cover the baking dish with foil and bake for 25-30 minutes. Remove the foil and bake for an additional 10-15 minutes until the cheese is melted and bubbly.</li>\n    <li>Let the casserole cool for a few minutes before serving.</li>\n  </ol>\n</div>"